list_page_teaser: What type of person could come up with this idea, of writing a program that draws people's personalities?  See for yourself by checking out a few of my Self-Portraits!
description_html: These are images of yours truly, Tom W. Hartung, the creator of this site!
story_html: Currently there is only one image, but if you look at my rather middle-of-the-road scores you can see that I am actually a versatile and flexible person. So I will be adding a few more images soon, as time permits.

image_list.subtitle_html: Creator of seeourminds.com
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: This image is based on the results of one of the first times I answered Keirsey's questionnaire.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.story_html:
This image is based on a score from one of the first times I took the Keirsey Temperament Sorter. Like others I have talked to, at first I was surprised to learn I was an INFP!

I have actually taken various versions of the quiz – this is kind of a hobby of mine – and have even written my own!.

Because this is my first self-portrait, it holds a special signifigance for me and is my favorite.
image_list.explain_dom: The Red in this image represents my preference for using emotion rather than logic to make decisions.  In Introverts, the auxiliary function is directed outwardly and is more evident than the dominant function.  Looking at the score scales, you can see that this is a very slight preference, allowing me to adapt and use logic when the situation calls for it.
image_list.explain_aux: The Blue in this image represents my preference for ideas over facts.  In Introverts, the dominant function is directed inwardly.  Compared to the other pairs of opposites, this is a fairly strong preference and shows up consistently when I take different versions of the various four-letter-type online quizzes.
